'''Daasanach''' (also known as Dasenech, Daasanech, Dathanaik, Dathanaic, Dathanik, Dhaasanac, Gheleba, Geleba, Geleb, Gelebinya, Gallab, Galuba, Gelab, Gelubba, Dama, Marille, Merile, Merille, Morille, Reshiat, Russia) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] [[language]] spoken  by the [[Daasanach people|Daasanach]] in [[Ethiopia]], [[South Sudan]] and [[Kenya]] whose homeland is along the Lower [[Omo River (Ethiopia)|Omo River]] and on the shores of [[Lake Turkana]].<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed.  2005.  ''Ethnologue:  Languages of the World''.  15th edition.  Dallas:  Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref>

