{{Infobox person | name = Hannah Allam | image = Hannah Allam at Women and Terrorism Roundtable.jpg | caption = Hannah Allam at [[United States House Committee on Homeland Security]] in 2016 | birthname = Hannah Allam | birth_date = 1977 | birth_place = [[Oklahoma]], USA | education = | occupation = Journalist | credits = }}
'''Hannah Allam''' (born 1977)<ref>{{cite news|last1=Allam|first1=Hannah|title=Oklahoma reporter strives for truth, safety in Iraq|url=http://newsok.com/oklahoma-reporter-strives-for-truth-safety-in-iraq/article/2874725|accessdate=23 November 2014|work=NewsOK|date=21 November 2004}}</ref> is an American [[journalist]] and reporter for BuzzFeed News who is based in Washington, DC. Allam was the [[Middle East]] Bureau Chief ([[Baghdad]]) for [[McClatchy Newspapers]].<ref>[http://www.mcclatchydc.com/hannah-allam/ Journalist page for Hannah Allam for McClatchy Newspapers]</ref> <ref name="uga">{{cite web|title=Correspondent for Iraq War to give 30th McGill Lecture|url=http://news.uga.edu/releases/article/correspondent-for-iraq-war-to-give-30th-mcgill-lecture/|website=UGA today|publisher=University of Georgia|accessdate=23 November 2014|date=8 June 2009}}</ref> Early in her career, Allam interned for the [[Washington Post]]. She then became a staff reporter for the [[St. Paul Pioneer Press]], from which [[McClatchy Newspapers|McClatchy]] recruited her in 2003 to assist them with, and later to lead, their in-depth coverage of the [[Iraq War]]. She is fluent in English, French, and [[Arabic]]. She was reared in [[Saudi Arabia]] and the [[United Arab Emirates]], but she returned to the USA to complete high school in [[Oklahoma]], then she majored in journalism and was editor of the student newspaper at the [[University of Oklahoma]].{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}
She was a 2008-2009 [[Nieman Fellow]] at [[Harvard University]].<ref>[http://www.nieman.harvard.edu/reports/article/101985/Reporting-the-Iraq-War-Whose-Truth-Is-Being-Told.aspx Nieman Reports, Winter 2009 | Online Exclusives, Access September 6, 2014]</ref><ref>[http://erniesuggsharvard.wordpress.com/2008/11/19/hannah-allam/ Journalist Ernie Suggs recalls Hannah Allam as 2009 Nieman Fellow at Harvard]</ref>
