'''Jean Krier''' (2 January 1949 – 12 January 2013) was a [[Luxembourg]] poet who in 2011 was awarded both the [[Adelbert von Chamisso Prize]] for the best work by a non-German author and the [[Servais Prize]] for the best literary work written by a Luxembourger.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dasgedichtblog.de/das-gedicht-trauert-um-seinen-autor-und-ehemaligen-redakteur-jean-krier-1949-2013/2013/01/15/|title=DAS GEDICHT trauert um seinen Autor und ehemaligen Redakteur Jean Krier (1949 – 2013)|date=15 January 2013|publisher=Das Gedicht. Zeitschrift für Lyrik, Essay und Kritik|language=German|accessdate=15 January 2013}}</ref> In both cases, the work in question was ''Herzens Lust Spiele'' (2010).<ref>[http://www.wort.lu/wort/web/letzebuerg/artikel/2011/03/145926/noch-ein-preis-fuer-jean-krier.php "Noch ein Preis für Jean Krier"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324012025/http://www.wort.lu/wort/web/letzebuerg/artikel/2011/03/145926/noch-ein-preis-fuer-jean-krier.php |date=2012-03-24 }}, ''Luxemburger Wort'', 23 March 2011. {{de icon}} Retrieved 24 March 2011.</ref> In connection with the Chamisso prize, the jury commented on how the work provided an original and impressive enrichment of German-language poetry. "His carpets of German, subtly interspersed with sprinkles of French, are fed by experiential elements and reading experiences".<ref>[http://www.goethe.de/kue/lit/nac/en7250086.htm Vaclav Demling, "Chamisso Prize Goes To Jean Krier (02/26/2011)"], ''Goethe Institut'', February 2011. Retrieved 24 March 2011.</ref>
Krier was born in [[Luxembourg (city)|Luxembourg City]], studied German and English literature in [[Freiburg]], and lived and worked in Luxembourg. He contributed poems to German-language publications such as NDL (NeueDeutscheLyriker), Manuskripte: Zeitschrift für Literatur, [[Akzente|Akzente: Zeitschrift für Dichtung]], Das Gedicht: Zeitschrift für Lyrik, Essay und Kritik and Poet-magazin.<ref>[http://www.poetenladen.de/jean-krier.htm "Jean Krier"], ''Poetenladen''. Retrieved 24 March 2011.</ref>
==Works== *"''Herzens Lust Spiele''", poetenladen, Leipzig, 2010 *"''Gefundenes Fressen''", Rimbaud, Aachen, 2005 *"''Tableaux/Sehstücke''", Gollenstein, Blieskastel, 2002 *"''Bretonische Inseln''", Landpresse, Weilerswist, 1995
