{{Infobox language | name = Munichi | altname = Muniche | states = Peru | region = [[Loreto Region|Loreto]] | extinct = late 1990s, with the death of Victoria Huancho Icahuate | familycolor = American | family = Macro-[[Arawakan languages|Arawakan]] ? | iso3 = myr | glotto = muni1258 | glottorefname = Muniche | map = Muniche language.png | mapcaption = Location of Munichi }}
'''Munichi''' is a recently extinct language which was spoken in the village of Munichis, about 10 miles (16&nbsp;km) west of [[Yurimaguas]], [[Loreto Region]], [[Peru]]. In 1988, there were two mother-tongue speakers, but they had not met since the 1970s. The last known fluent speaker, Victoria Huancho Icahuate, died in the late 1990s. As of 2009 there were several semi-speakers who retained significant lexical, and partial grammatical, knowledge of the language (Michael et al. 2013).
== Classification == The language is considered an isolate (Michael et al. 2013), but the [[pronominal]] [[suffixes]] bear a close resemblance to those reconstructed for proto-[[Arawakan]] (Gibson 1996:18-19), and some lexical items are similar to ones in Arawakan languages (Jolkesky 2016:310-317). Although Jolkesky (''id''.) argues that the language belongs to a putative Macro-Arawakan stock, evidence has yet to be provided for placing it either in a sister branch to the Arawakan language family or in a branch within this language family. There is substantial borrowing from the local variety of [[Quechua languages|Quechua]], and to a lesser extent from [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Cahuapanan languages]] (Michael et al. 2013).
== Phonology == Munichi has six vowels: /a, e, i, ɨ, o, u/.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://linguistics.berkeley.edu/~saphon|title=SAPhon – South American Phonological Inventories|website=linguistics.berkeley.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-08-12}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |+Consonants ! colspan="2" | ![[Bilabial consonant|Bilabial]] ![[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]] ![[Palato-alveolar consonant|Palato-alveolar]] ![[Retroflex consonant|Retroflex]] ![[Palatal consonant|Palatal]] ![[Velar consonant|Velar]] ![[Glottal consonant|Glottal]] |- ! rowspan="2" |[[Stop consonant|Stop]] !<small>voiceless</small> |p |t | | |c |k |ʔ |- ![[Voice (phonetics)|<small>voiced</small>]] | |d | | | |g | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Affricate consonant|Affricate]] | |t͡s |t͡ʃ |ʈʂ | | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Fricative consonant|Fricative]] | |s |ʃ |ʂ |ç | |h |- ! colspan="2" |[[Nasal consonant|Nasal]] |m |n | | |ɲ | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Approximant consonant|Approximant]] | |l | | |j |w | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Flap consonant|Flap]] | |ɾ | | | | | |}
